{"type":"message","id":"28c542a4","parentId":"6245e322","timestamp":"2026-03-11T22:38:31.669Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hsiv8xit8txi_1","toolName":"message","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Validation failed for tool \"message\":\n  - action: must be equal to one of the allowed values\n\nReceived arguments:\n{\n  \"action\": \"sendAttachment\",\n  \"media\": \"/Users/suchuanlei/.openclaw/workspace/slide-deck/feishu-asset-workflow/feishu-asset-workflow.pptx\",\n  \"target\": \"ou_0eb8fd7529b5669c0a2de183a76a760f\"\n}"}],"details":{},"isError":true,"timestamp":1773268711660}}
{"type":"message","id":"7aaa8a8c","parentId":"28c542a4","timestamp":"2026-03-11T22:38:36.420Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to use a different action. Let me check the correct action. According to the tools, I should use `message send` but it doesn't support file paths. Let me check if there's a way to send files. Actually, looking at the tool description more carefully, I should use the feishu-send-file skill instead.Actually, let me check what message actions are available. Looking at the message tool - it has `send`, `react`, `reactions`, `delete`, `unsend`. It doesn't have `sendAttachment`.\n\nLooking at the available skills, there's a `feishu-send-file` skill that should handle this. Let me use that instead.","thinkingSignature":"9251de8869c1a259bba670468a02fea7a996df7ab0602c88ee30c44399a90205"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mqlp5h4vkhuk_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/suchuanlei/.agents/skills/feishu-send-file/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":34798,"output":185,"cacheRead":43910,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78893,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773268711669}}
{"type":"message","id":"8fee8284","parentId":"7aaa8a8c","timestamp":"2026-03-11T22:38:36.438Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mqlp5h4vkhuk_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: feishu-send-file\ndescription: >\n  Send files to a Feishu group or user via REST API. Use when the user\n  explicitly asks to send a file, attachment, or document to a Feishu\n  chat/group. Triggers: \"发文件到飞书\", \"把这个文件发到群里\",\n  \"send file to feishu\", \"发个附件\".\n  NOT for: sending text messages (use message tool), sending images/screenshots\n  (use feishu-screenshot skill), or reading documents (use feishu-doc skill).\n---\n\n# Feishu Send File\n\nSend files to Feishu chats via REST API (bypasses the built-in message tool limitation for file messages).\n\n## Steps\n\n### 1. Get tenant_access_token\n\n```python\nimport json, os, requests\n\nconfig_path = os.path.expanduser('~/.openclaw-autoclaw/openclaw.json')\nwith open(config_path) as f:\n    cfg = json.load(f)\n\nfeishu = cfg['channels']['feishu']\nr = requests.post(\n    'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal',\n    json={'app_id': feishu['appId'], 'app_secret': feishu['appSecret']}\n)\ntoken = r.json()['tenant_access_token']\n```\n\n### 2. Upload the file\n\n```python\nwith open('/path/to/your/file', 'rb') as f:\n    r2 = requests.post(\n        'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/im/v1/files',\n        headers={'Authorization': f'Bearer {token}'},\n        data={'file_type': 'stream', 'file_name': 'filename.ext'},\n        files={'file': ('filename.ext', f, 'application/octet-stream')}\n    )\nfile_key = r2.json()['data']['file_key']\n```\n\nSupported `file_type` values: `opus`, `mp4`, `pdf`, `doc`, `xls`, `ppt`, `stream` (generic)\n\n### 3. Send file message to chat\n\n```python\nchat_id = 'oc_xxxx'  # target chat_id\n\nr3 = requests.post(\n    'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/im/v1/messages',\n    headers={'Authorization': f'Bearer {token}', 'Content-Type': 'application/json'},\n    params={'receive_id_type': 'chat_id'},\n    json={\n        'receive_id': chat_id,\n        'msg_type': 'file',\n        'content': json.dumps({'file_key': file_key})\n    }\n)\nprint(r3.json())\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- The bot can only download files it **uploaded itself** (`234008` error otherwise)\n- Images use a different endpoint: `POST /im/v1/images` with `image_type=message`\n- To send an image message, use `msg_type: image` and `content: {\"image_key\": \"...\"}`\n- Required scope: `im:message:send_as_bot`, `im:resource`\n\n## References\n\n- https://open.feishu.cn/document/uAjLw4CM/ukTMukTMukTM/reference/im-v1/file/create\n- https://open.feishu.cn/document/uAjLw4CM/ukTMukTMukTM/reference/im-v1/message/create\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773268716433}}
{"type":"message","id":"0266a961","parentId":"8fee8284","timestamp":"2026-03-11T22:38:45.821Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me use this skill to send the file. I'll need to get the token, upload the file, then send it to the user.","thinkingSignature":"a988a9f1653d7908c647900a1b6e3305b8d7386db75cba5934bcfa457c86c6f7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6iggrozkn2j1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nimport json, os, requests\n\nconfig_path = os.path.expanduser('~/.openclaw-autoclaw/openclaw.json')\nwith open(config_path) as f:\n    cfg = json.load(f)\n\nfeishu = cfg['channels']['feishu']\nr = requests.post(\n    'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal',\n    json={'app_id': feishu['appId'], 'app_secret': feishu['appSecret']}\n)\ntoken = r.json()['tenant_access_token']\nprint(\"Token:\", token[:20] + \"...\")\n\n# Upload file\nwith open('/Users/suchuanlei/.openclaw/workspace/slide-deck/feishu-asset-workflow/feishu-asset-workflow.pptx', 'rb') as f:\n    r2 = requests.post(\n        'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/im/v1/files',\n        headers={'Authorization': f'Bearer {token}'},\n        data={'file_type': 'ppt', 'file_name': '飞书文档资产化工作流.pptx'},\n        files={'file': ('飞书文档资产化工作流.pptx', f, 'application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.presentationml.presentation')}\n    )\nprint(\"Upload:\", r2.json())\nfile_key = r2.json()['data']['file_key']\n\n# Send to user (open_id)\nr3 = requests.post(\n    'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/im/v1/messages',\n    headers={'Authorization': f'Bearer {token}', 'Content-Type': 'application/json'},\n    params={'receive_id_type': 'open_id'},\n    json={\n        'receive_id': 'ou_0eb8fd7529b5669c0a2de183a76a760f',\n        'msg_type': 'file',\n        'content': json.dumps({'file_key': file_key})\n    }\n)\nprint(\"Send:\", r3.json())\nPY","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":35701,"output":487,"cacheRead":43910,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80098,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773268716438}}
