ebugging options**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I need to read debug HTML or install a package. The yellow line seems to suggest an installation, but I should confirm the requirements first. I wonder if using debug HTML could be a better approach — maybe I can use saved markdown instead, or check if a tool partially saved the output? It makes sense to inspect the output files first to see what's available.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"微信这破壳又开始作妖了，正文抓到了标题，但在下载配图时被代理依赖卡住了。问题不大，本王先直接读它落下来的调试页，把正文抠出来。","textSignature":"msg_05af7521743ea8dd0169b2039b85ac81968080d46ceb3e2126"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3sUs8rmCTeoegXXI4kak2FmR|fc_05af7521743ea8dd0169b2039b9c4c8196a3a45b840e96892a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.agent-reach/tools/wechat-article-for-ai && find output -maxdepth 3 -type f | tail -20 && echo '---' && wc -c output/debug/* 2>/dev/null | tail -5"},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"cd ~/.agent-reach/tools/wechat-article-for-ai && find output -maxdepth 3 -type f | tail -20 && echo '---' && wc -c output/debug/* 2>/dev/null | tail -5\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":718,"output":178,"cacheRead":86656,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87552,"cost":{"input":0.0012565,"output":0.002492,"cacheRead":0.015164799999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0189133}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773273999620}}
