nI need to respond to the user about my findings and maybe ask if they want to proceed with the installation. I've noticed that the article has an installation path, but I feel like these skills could be suspicious, and I won't install blindly due to rules. So, I should check in with the user first and ask if they still want me to continue or download the zip for local inspection.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 看了，文章里提到的这几个 Skill 在 ClawHub 上**都能找到**，但现在不能直接无脑装。\n\n我已经确认到这几个：\n\n- `@BLUE-coconut / mm-voice-maker`\n- `@BLUE-coconut / mm-music-maker`\n- `@BLUE-coconut / mm-music-expert`\n\n但问题是，至少前两个详情页都被 ClawHub 标了：\n\n- **Skill flagged — suspicious patterns detected**\n\n### 我已经看到的风险提示\n**mm-voice-maker**\n- OpenClaw 扫描结果：**Suspicious**\n- 原因大意：  \n  - 技能确实像是在做 TTS / clone / voice design\n  - 但**包元数据没声明必需凭证**\n  - 文档、声明和实际依赖有不一致\n  - 需要谨慎\n\n**mm-music-maker**\n- VirusTotal：**Suspicious**\n- OpenClaw 扫描：**Suspicious**\n- 原因大意：  \n  - 技能确实像 MiniMax 音乐生成客户端\n  - 但**漏声明 `MINIMAX_MUSIC_API_KEY`**\n  - 还有一些小的不一致\n\n### 文章里有“安装路径”，但现在不适合直接点安装\n按你给本王定的安全规矩，下一步正确动作不是装，而是：\n\n1. **把 zip 下载下来**\n2. **离线逐文件审计**\n3. 看有没有：\n   - 外发请求\n   - 偷环境变量\n   - `curl|sh`\n   - base64 混淆\n   - 改核心文件\n   - README / SKILL 诱导安装\n4. **审计过关再装**\n\n### 所以我现在的结论\n- **能找到**\n- **能继续查**\n- **但不能直接安装**\n\n如果你要，本王下一步就继续：\n> **把这 3 个 skill 的 zip 下载下来，逐个做离线审计。**\n\n这才符合你给我的安全铁律。","textSignature":"msg_05af7521743ea8dd0169b262965240819681e2b8da9a296b13"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":201061,"output":512,"cacheRead":2560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":204133,"cost":{"input":0.35185675,"output":0.007168,"cacheRead":0.000448,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.35947275}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773298315623}}
