{"type":"message","id":"eb276b06","parentId":"9a2ca66a","timestamp":"2026-03-12T06:53:33.950Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering skill auditing**\n\nI need to respond regarding whether to continue with the audit or installation process. The user might be thinking about using \"clawdefender.\" While that's a skill, they asked how to proceed with downloading ZIP files and auditing them. I wonder if I should check out \"skill-vetter\" too, focusing on its security-first approach to skill vetting before any installation. It seems like reading up on one specific skill is crucial before moving forward.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_05af7521743ea8dd0169b262e6f60c8196afeb1038f018541a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpsmLqBX2b9xRN9SlX-IiTeX_Amhcrwj4K4cmGaKNIVmtADNlGj7mrXCX3Ft1h4HMqXd3ODIcM4L6rXg_AhhvV0PtVvU7pf0Y3Id-ckiqqN9xISOI3dVqUHMrbhLgMAscTnBv6OG5sEiAxsWSuX4BmMgLr9fViAS2i9byh74g1UA46STEsHgYy9b4JQCb61ZOETt06_tX3u44xQEzAl8rag7bVpWmjJh2MxZPtGI9r279mI4ITa2cqO42tq9XKIvPSOV7iMwLLsVwhyVXl-Acbvbp2CHknbJu9L7eNkfQjrKEp-hG9nqGe22yGRq1DFPkSaSH6Oe3kqJBn_3HxA27VwdDQ8q0rxRKWheics_pTRHcpG5G-rygy1zkr82pR-N--BDBJqWnCyfHkVcuP8DVp7-q3rkptiMgbj7Y-4riHA3LQvUZ0UC6S8pO4D9FkeNRrIcXOuFCAIv5dsYufCP87B2aZF4apolG_ZAWwhCCGNXaYI4FQ8zDlPfgNvoGIAWSnWKwSj_cMMmMQNLildD0j09dTLX4u6Ih1lypxO9sHCPhmUAYe2NNPNItH6xiPPd6BVOmAzjiw5u0kYDJi3qSaiGn4qOo6e0SBv1GJyG7jR4LV7JIKKzBDJbXeU3_uZQpp4HFeDV3xP4_ZRBB5DjeYM66-VF3pcRewLSaa2XejfxdeCyOx6qiN9eBJHXAafqN8PKxix9VwUk_OUXfcfhN6DcCXfq-tbdrDKRbqJQusGyV-YI0rFkLoxlMlOBp1A9hJOpofbLyOHCgh1U3cHKCY9XJotx2sBQ1ntVL9ugtFy64ihZgPHLHmgNzCBD-PC0xRbnoBxnPnE3fVYbFScCeseQsQlzeQ_zBK27PJzFYy_2lcAT5MLgAReWqBtojZRQFOCa_lDx1EqpxvcxmZ_-7sqC21QNsCbp_UhIjJ6wb3hz6dlHYdZB_6nNyWU0a4ypVlJkRm9NtgeV419YAckXPFm_PI7Kpu6IrCq-Ic5Kh09j2IuGjOh1hre9I1dO8H3EugGvV1Zr41wM6DZFXVcc2O030HlojtzGhHQYAh4EqVJGgpEDvmkwjWW22u71QBbbdUtBUMwvDzA6SvOeMv4knzgjifYn8t5Ug3B7IavWpKMN0B-uzJFubdgHPaiPPerDQY6lYUqi1Y-dC0JHwLfs9YM05rfmecXKyTSeaxL4Ze_DRAu_lNMiVLCL1pV29WCUAFTePp\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering skill auditing**\\n\\nI need to respond regarding whether to continue with the audit or installation process. The user might be thinking about using \\\"clawdefender.\\\" While that's a skill, they asked how to proceed with downloading ZIP files and auditing them. I wonder if I should check out \\\"skill-vetter\\\" too, focusing on its security-first approach to skill vetting before any installation. It seems like reading up on one specific skill is crucial before moving forward.\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_joQGNksEgoCzJOvk9Nk7dOK4|fc_05af7521743ea8dd0169b262eabda48196b6545097cf187f7f","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/suchuanlei/.openclaw/workspace/skills/skill-vetter/SKILL.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/Users/suchuanlei/.openclaw/workspace/skills/skill-vetter/SKILL.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":159105,"output":100,"cacheRead":45568,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":204773,"cost":{"input":0.27843375,"output":0.0014,"cacheRead":0.0079744,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.28780815}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773298398720}}
{"type":"message","id":"e2d905ba","parentId":"eb276b06","timestamp":"2026-03-12T06:53:33.972Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_joQGNksEgoCzJOvk9Nk7dOK4|fc_05af7521743ea8dd0169b262eabda48196b6545097cf187f7f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: skill-vetter\nversion: 1.0.0\ndescription: Security-first skill vetting for AI agents. Use before installing any skill from ClawHub, GitHub, or other sources. Checks for red flags, permission scope, and suspicious patterns.\n---\n\n# Skill Vetter 🔒\n\nSecurity-first vetting protocol for AI agent skills. **Never install a skill without vetting it first.**\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Before installing any skill from ClawHub\n- Before running skills from GitHub repos\n- When evaluating skills shared by other agents\n- Anytime you're asked to install unknown code\n\n## Vetting Protocol\n\n### Step 1: Source Check\n\n- Where did this skill come from?\n- Is the author known/reputable?\n- How many downloads/stars does it have?\n- When was it last updated?\n\n### Step 2: Code Review (MANDATORY)\n\nRead ALL files in the skill. Check for these **RED FLAGS**:\n\n🚨 REJECT IMMEDIATELY IF YOU SEE:\n- curl/wget to unknown URLs\n- Sends data to external servers\n- Requests credentials/tokens/API keys\n- Reads ~/.ssh, ~/.aws, ~/.config without clear reason\n- Accesses MEMORY.md, USER.md, SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md\n- Uses base64 decode on anything\n- Uses eval() or exec() with external input\n- Modifies system files outside workspace\n- Installs packages without listing them\n- Network calls to IPs instead of domains\n- Obfuscated code (compressed, encoded, minified)\n- Requests elevated/sudo permissions\n- Accesses browser cookies/sessions\n\n### Step 3: Permission Scope\n\n- What files does it need to read/write?\n- What commands does it run?\n- Does it need network access? To where?\n- Is the scope minimal for its stated purpose?\n\n### Step 4: Risk Classification\n\n| Risk Level | Examples | Action |\n|------------|----------|--------|\n| 🟢 LOW | Notes, weather, formatting | Basic review, install OK |\n| 🟡 MEDIUM | File ops, browser, APIs | Full code review required |\n| 🔴 HIGH | Credentials, trading, system | Human approval required |\n| ⛔ EXTREME | Security configs, root access | Do NOT install |\n\n## Output Format\n\nAfter vetting, produce:\n\n```\nSKILL VETTING REPORT\n═══════════════════════════════════════\nSkill: [name]\nSource: [ClawHub / GitHub / other]\nRisk Level: [🟢/🟡/🔴/⛔]\nRed Flags: [None / List]\nVerdict: [✅ SAFE / ⚠️ CAUTION / ❌ REJECT]\n═══════════════════════════════════════\n```\n\n*Paranoia is a feature.* 🔒\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773298413962}}
{"type":"message","id":"802ef1f2","parentId":"e2d905ba","timestamp":"2026-03-12T06:53:46.271Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering download options**\n\nI need to audit or download something and I'm weighing my options. Should I use browser downloads or curl? It might be easier to get direct download URLs from a page. I'll probably need to read all the files, so maybe I'll use write to download and unzip them. Since exec is allowed, I should avoid installing anything new. Downloading zips to /tmp seems smart, starting with mm-voice-maker first. I’ll look for those download URLs on the pages.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_05af7521743ea8dd0169b262f259dc8196b8683fef61dcb70c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpsmL3z19D1cZjeWza5jcxodXItvvRBrRDAY1-H-1mesi1siVFzAvkYkmrHTeoyS1dShSOjJUbcc899hgAOXnoZN51xY9vfgsfxpnH5qSO5_pXWDa9hvw2N_pZYY4mYDJ94k5F4tJC9qUqr-ehqRs_EYFBNMindVPQm6FR9QlVSYaIhoIAQ-Wb0woee5_lOQZa377Xslom6Bhw-VyyRUKtkkQN1hZzq86FXRh-YV8VU781XzWK1QL1rYaL7TvtAWS8JQYHvkDVYjSn0z-xvfjikY1oEouvhil0w-vlUKuVj7hg7a6rQT1bujgni3OaqPyxhemOIZeqXaN_PZBwyf-Gvvu2bZBvYPQD2LqT-xnnI6vU5pHyunwkBa9zPuF5M2VWWACvd5_WOX4NGnlDnVlLbxv1r4Uf3YlPs2sVU7eQ0lVhoX1uP-wT7kvpt6jwW-b70R3HUIXeTsa5GHpc9y8rBj8y8HqlvhY9v7Ht1NGCy7PdggWfU9LUw8Jh2gjhO7Z1d0gZaE0jPOgDWWd8SX6BVLb_FQdMTh4LZHXMvIrhJFN3W5CK8KNoWZ-_0yFroFgexTZ7dqv0e6N8QN0RCApZ0fXKTJUaVvisPDr9oejNxnik8fnwonMwGzbhl2-3KLqs3BbmsIYlhrYI0p6zAPAika-Q6tiVTmws8aRRCk8FZyFPYqihX8sp0mbYaOd5tDGQ7YmExygAJO7hC-AR4x9by2x4Cduz_xnpqgk6MIgtx475T7Zl7awipdNC2-FfxMm_DHCO5awAviB2egI3zW6boKeVsdRZKexnAKSRpdZIUqGr-3IP0U98Mue95RwN_FIR63QAVzGLVA-U4-QHo0XXWvbKdyUWlzHsJGGcq1o0l4iu9PrcLMEEf3hMkmzn9BZ9In8dcAvyTyP7wgHTr2XH_znVOVaOhNk8IOTNKG1wYLr64wAW3alS9duMW2_z-yv9WJ_DOwbzfPjqlwYcfr6_rEehxNMhYXTqt5QaLpdoLCB3MJz2nae6W7W9uo4aM-8oI4QlF9YOG9K9pIcXA-2TGiIajvzYISY0HnsZ0aLnMr8xASSb8p1gyOLEQTNCADuVoc_ZCHM038UDC6W-bqJ3jXRL75SuvEbwWmU7OnCEoT6FP7vPR6bfVqILfNBmFMaebUSALNWV9BlfF8h0tIVV173xGoTXYY0weqmDepMdVvuZZeveGUMo4HZo