{"type":"message","id":"2ab4dc75","parentId":"2dc345cf","timestamp":"2026-03-12T13:19:17.126Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Evaluating document updates**\n\nI need to use the feishu-update-doc and feishu_doc_media insert tools. I'll probably fetch the document ID from the earlier created document URL. It seems I'll need to insert images at headings too. However, I find that feishu_doc_media only appends images at the end, and feishu_update_doc supports inserting images with a local path. I might need to upload the images to a drive for accessible URLs, but that complicates things since the user is looking for proper image placement.\n\n**Considering document image insertion**\n\nI’m considering using the update_doc selection_by_title and insert_after methods with markdown for images. If local paths aren't supported, that would cause issues. The user asked for image insertion, so I need to be aware of the tool limitations. I might just append at the end and not correspond to positions, but maybe I could use browser automation to paste images directly. It looks more complex, but browser automation in the Feishu doc UI seems feasible, even if it takes time. I’ll read through the relevant skills for this.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_05af7521743ea8dd0169b2bd49cd58819698c0bb57bb8abad3\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpsr1UHE1bq5y7EPC3MWR0jT9LYt5_OrZq3ebd5be8LapqyqDoc8OGwmuloFCJIuRYd6yqJsFfDgHJ_wMvOwzvQD9qe7ltPl9IzAQhgsdhIeg4Dw5wk21yHb-DH_plRr-aDStvf7sFKYc3PoJg-vsnd2B-9vtK_czsfVp-GbqokFkQwBi2fRdxA7cECOiJiXELWgQl4kMSm4QWI9b5M7N8a3hb19DvO_c8kXQVhLnfLfBGPg343DEtt4FMabOKKSPf8GZizkt-3oDbAZ_RKW-loz0IC6VBRCYYZhqNDXSKXcKQ3OXcG2wNRU68w7plz9-Mlola-LGOD2QnAEjfwjojE4qigaewhk5QvLvpuGrR0hsidSG3tcOS11ACdFsVt7Hd7yIUOrp0lIBCCb7s0jd49bowqD6goQ0kIeBXWz8wx378nHWgvAcyPh5A6rtM0grK99Spc9XssmOWJsnuzkMQd5o0UZmu3a6xg-QptMSP8VP13r9Fo0bR7M2uM4HsTW6rAxYRAc5mrvMJygfETzY8y5A4P2C5pBM6XAgfWjKAlwE7QXzBzBaoPEvuutsOSyVZ7iONiAcBerwJ-ZQ